/2019/nov/28/dhruva-sarja-to-resume-work-for-pogaru-15751.html|title=Dhruva Sarja to resume work for Pogaru|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-11-30}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background: #ffc;\" |''[[Sultan (2020 film)|Sultan]]'' {{dagger}}\n|{{TBA}}\n|Bakkiyaraj Kannan\n|[[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n|Post-production, Tamil Debut<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/karthis-sultan-to-hit-screens-during-summer-holidays/articleshow/73297255.cms</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/sultan-rashmika-mandanna-confirms-the-title-of-her-next-film-with-karthi-1581520-2019-08-16|title=Sultan: Rashmika Mandanna confirms the title of her next film with Karthi|newspaper=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21|agency=Ist}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background: #ffc;\" |''[[AA20 (2020 film)|AA 20]] {{dagger}}''\n|{{TBA}}\n|[[Sukumar (director)|Sukumar]]\n|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|Filming\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Language\n! Film\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n| [[South Indian International Movie Awards|South Indian International Movie Awards for Best Debut Actress (Leading Role)]]\n| rowspan=\"7\" | [[Kannada language|Kannada]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Kirik Party]]''\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[IIFA Utsavam|IIFA Utsavam Award for Best Actress]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2018\n| [[Awards|Luv Lavike Readers Choice Award for Best Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Anjani Putra]]''\n| rowspan=2 {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Zee Kannada|Zee Kannada Hemmeya Kannadathi Award for Best Actress]]\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Kannada|Filmfare Awards South for Best Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]''\n| rowspan=2 {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[SIIMA Award for Best Actress - Kannada|South Indian International Movie Awards for Bes]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Kodava people]]\n[[Category:People from Kodagu district]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:SIIMA Awards winners]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Telugu cinema]]\n[[SIIMA Award for Best Actress - Kannada|t Actress in Leading Role]]\n|-\n|[[Awards|TSR TV9 National Award for Best Actress]] \n|{{Nominated}} \n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\" | 2019\n|[[Filmibeat|Filmibeat Award for Best Debutant Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"8\" |[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|''[[Chalo]]''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[Zee Cine Awards|Zee Cine Awards for Favorite Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" |''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[Awards|Sri Kala Sudha Telugu Awards for Best Debut Heroine]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA Award for Best Actress]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Award|JFW award - Sensational Actor]]\n|{{Won}}<ref>VBJ JFW Awards 2019: Yet Another Unforgettable Success! https://jfwonline.com/article/vbj-jfw-awards-2019-yet-another-unforgettable-success/</ref>\n|-\n|[[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South|Filmfare Awards South Best Actress Critics Choice]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[Awards|Behindwoods Gold Medal (Best Actor Critics Choice)]]\n|''[[Dear Comrade]]''\n|{{Won}}<ref name=\"BG\"/>\n|-\n|}\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Rashmika Mandanna}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=8612305|title=Rashmika Mandanna}}\n\n{{SIIMA Award for Best Female D\u00e9butante}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{short description|Indian actress and model}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Rashmika Mandanna\n| caption            = Mandanna at the ''Dear Comrade'' Press Meet in 2019\n| image              = Rashmika Mandanna PYTV press meet.jpg\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1996|04|05}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Rashmika-Mandanna|title=Rashmika Mandanna: Movies, Photos, Videos, News & Biography \u2013 eTimes|website=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Virajpet]], [[Karnataka]], India\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|model}}\n| years_active       = 2016\u2013present\n}}\n'''Rashmika Mandanna''' (born 5 April 1996) is an Indian film actress and [[model (person)|model]] who works predominantly in [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] and [[Kannada cinema|Kannada]] films. She is popularly dubbed by the [[Mass media|media]] and [[Kannada film industry]] as the 'India's Crush'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/metrolife/metrolife-on-the-move/the-outrage-against-rashmika-is-unnecessary-751971.html|title=The outrage against Rashmika is unnecessary|date=4 August 2019|website=Deccan Herald}}</ref><ref name=\"Rosh\">{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-is-the-bangalore-times-most-desirable-woman-2017/amp_articleshow/63129397.cms|title=The Belageddu song from Kirik Party had you dubbed as the \u2018Karnataka Crush\u2019. Your reaction to that?|work=timesofindia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-is-the-bangalore-times-most-desirable-woman-2017/articleshow/63129397.cms|title=Rashmika Mandanna is the Bangalore Times Most Desirable Woman 2017 \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> Rashmika is one among very few actresses to have a film gross \u20b91 billion in such a short span<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/sep/03/rashmika-mandanna-lands-in-crorepati-club-1866645.amp|title=Rashmika Mandanna lands in crorepati club|work=newindianexpress}}</ref> and one of the most popular and highest-paid actresses in [[Tollywood (Telugu)|Telugu]] and [[Kannada]] cinema industry.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-joins-the-big-league-of-highest-paid-female-actors-in-tollywood/articleshow/69533649.cms|title=Rashmika Mandanna joins the big league of highest paid female actors in Tollywood - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/rashmika-mandana-becomes-one-sandalwood-s-highest-paid-women-actors-91985</ref>\n\nRashmika made her acting debut in [[Kannada]] 2016 film ''[[Kirik Party]]''. In 2017 she starred in two commercially successful films, ''[[Anjani Putra]]'' and ''[[Chamak]]''. Later she made her Telugu debut with romantic drama ''[[Chalo]]'' in 2018.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/chalo-week-1-box-office-collection-naga-shouryas-film-becomes-superhit-just-7-days-760085|title=Chalo week 1 box office collection: Naga Shourya's film becomes a superhit in just 7 days|first=Shekhar H.|last=Hooli|date=10 February 2018|website=International Business Times, India Edition|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> In the same year, she starred in the [[romcom]] film ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'', which has become one of the highest profit earners in Telugu cinema, which earned her wide recognition.<ref name=\"Gf\">{{cite web|url=https://amp.ibtimes.co.in/geetha-govindam-total-box-office-collection-area-wise-distributors-earnings-theatrical-rights-783819|title=The total collections of Geetha Govindam have reached Rs 130 crore gross at the worldwide box office in its lifetime|work=ibtimes}}</ref> Her third Telugu venture was multi-starrer big budget film titled ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]''.<ref name=\"Dev\">{{cite web|url=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:http://english.sakshi.com/entertainment/2018/10/15/devadas-final-collections-joins-50-crore-club|title=Devadas Final Collections: Joins 50 Crore Club|website=Webcache.googleusercontent.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> It marked her third consecutive successful film in the same year in [[Telugu film industry]] after achieving a first hat trick-hit in [[Kannada film industry]], established herself as one of the leading actresses of [[Language|Telugu and Kannada cinema]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/geetha-govindam-storms-box-office-enters-100-crore-club/articleshow/65571937.cms|title=Geetha Govindam box office collection: Vijay Deverakonda-Rashmika Mandanna starrer storms box-office, enters 100 crore club|work=ibtimes}}</ref>\n \nShe starred in the commercially successful films such as ''[[Kirik Party]]'' (2016), ''[[Anjani Putra]]'' (2017), ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]'' (2017), ''[[Chalo]]'' (2018), ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'' (2018), ''[[Yajamana (2019 film)|Yajamana]]'' (2019), ''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]'' (2020) and ''[[Bheeshma (2020 film)|Bheeshma]]'' (2020)<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bheeshma-3-day-box-office-collection-nithiin-achieves-what-vijays-wfl-couldnt-813820</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sarileru-neekevvaru-6-day-box-office-collection-mahesh-babus-sln-makes-100-recovery-811829|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru 6-day box office collection: Mahesh Babu's SLN makes 100% recovery|website=International Business Times|date=17 January 2020|access-date=17 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2018/before-rashmika-mandanna-these-actresses-were-trolled-for-sexist-reasons-275854.html|title=Before Rashmika Mandanna, These Actresses Were Trolled For Sexist Reasons|first=Roktim|last=Rajpal|date=31 July 2018|website=Filmibeat.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> The back to back success of films has made her one of the most sought-after actresses in [[Cinema of South India|south Indian film industry]].<ref>https://www.google.sakshi.com/amp/story/entertainment%252F2018%252F12%252F23%252Frashmika-nithiin-bheeshma-update</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nRashmika Mandanna was born on 5 April 1996 as the elder daughter of Suman and Madan Mandanna in [[Virajpet]], a town in [[Kodagu district]] of [[Karnataka]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sharadhaa|first1=A.|title=Rashmika mandanna says it\u2019s all luck by chance|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2016/dec/20/rashmika-mandanna-says-its-all-luck-by-chance-1551322--1.html|website=The New Indian Express|accessdate=31 March 2017|date=21 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/sandalwood/200416/a-reel-virajpet-beauty.html|title=A reel Virajpet beauty|date=20 April 2016|work=www.deccanchronicle.com}}</ref> She did her schooling in Coorg Public School (COPS), Kodagu before she pursued [[pre-university course]] in Mysore Institute of commerce and arts, she has bachelor's degree in Psychology, Journalism and English Literature from [[Ramaiah Institute of Technology|Ramaiah college of Arts, Science and Commerce]], along with her studies she was doing modeling and appeared in a couple of advertisements.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/amp?params=LzIwMTcvMDcvMDQvNTk3NTk2|title=Rakshit, Rashmika get engaged in Virajpete|work=deccanherald}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nRashmika got engaged to actor [[Rakshit Shetty]]. They began dating during making of ''Kirik Party'' and got engaged on 3 July 2017 in a private ceremony in her hometown of Virajpet.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/content/620787/rakshit-rashmika-get-engaged-virajpet.html|title=Rakshit, Rashmika get engaged in Virajpet|date=2017-07-04|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-11-30}}</ref> The couple mutually broke off their engagement in September 2018, citing compatibility issues.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/rashmika-mandanna-calls-off-engagement-with-rakshit-shetty-1335970-2018-09-09|title=Rashmika Mandanna calls of engagement with Rakshit Shetty|work=www.indiatoday.com}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nRashmika began modelling in 2012. She won the [[Clean & Clear]] Fresh Face of India title the same year and was made the brand ambassador of [[Clean & Clear]]. Then she got the title of TVC in Lamode Bangalore's top model hunt 2013. Her pictures from the competition impressed the makers of the film ''[[Kirik Party]]'' who then cast her as the female lead for the film in early 2014. \n{{quote box|align=right|width=25em|quote = \"I was just 19 when I shot for the film. I am more like Saanvi (her character name) in real life, mature beyond my age; so it didn't feel tough.\"| source =\u2014 Rashmika shared her maiden flick ''[[Kirik Party]]'' experience.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dundoo |first1=Sangeetha Devi |title=Rashmika Mandanna\u2019s license to dream |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/rashmika-mandanna-talks-about-geetha-govindam-devadas-dear-comrade-and-how-cinema-has-changed-her-life/article24665502.ece |website=The Hindu |date=11 August 2018}}</ref>}} In an interview with ''[[The Times of India]]'', she recalled: \"The makers of Kirik Party saw a picture of mine from the Clean & Clear Fresh Face of India 2012 competition \u2014 one in which I was dancing during the college round \u2014 and approached me to act in the film. So, it really got things going. I always wanted to be in films.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/rashmika-mandanna-on-her-debut/articleshow/56137743.cms|title=Meet Saanvi, the hottie from Kirik Party|website=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref> She was cast as Saanvi Joseph, a college-goer, and the love interest of Karna (played by [[Rakshit Shetty]]).\n\n===Kannada debut and breakthrough (2016\u201317)===\nRashmika made her debut with ''[[Kirik Party]]'' in 2016, which opened to widespread acclaim from critics and audiences alike and went on to become [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing film]] of the year by collecting \u20b950 [[crore]]<ref name=\"ittt\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/rakshit-shettys-kirik-party-telugu-remake-rights-sold-talks-other-language-rights-721075|title=Rakshit Shetty's Kirik Party dubbed by malayalam movie premam and Telugu remake rights sold; talks on for other language rights|publisher=International Business Times|date=28 March 2017|accessdate=28 March 2017}}</ref> against production budget \u20b94 crore,<ref name=th>{{cite web|title=The budget of \u2018Kirik Party\u2019 would be around \u20b94crore|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/rakshith-shettys-kirik-party-to-go-on-the-floors-in-march/article8191273.ece\n|work=The Hindu}}</ref> and completed 150-days in main centers of [[Karnataka]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/krik-party-rakshit-shetty-rashmika-mandanna-celebrate-150-days-981176-2017-06-06|title=Kirik Party completes 150 days: Rakshit Shetty, Rashmika Mandanna celebrate with fans|website=India Today}}</ref> alongside Rashmika's performance received praise for her performance as Saanvi. The writer Sunayana Suresh of ''[[The Times of India]]'' states that \"Rashmika Mandanna as Saanvi is easy that pin-up girl in college and she breathes her path.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/kirik-party/movie-review/56250634.cms|title=Kirik Party Movie Review|work=The Times of India}}</ref> The film's reviewer for ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' wrote, \"Rashmika Mandanna has outshone in the film along with the main character\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2016/dec/31/youngsters-live-the-kirik-life-here-1554624--2.html|title=Youngsters Live The Kirik Life Here|work=The New Indian Express|date=31 December 2016}}</ref> The ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]''`s Shashiprasad noted that \"Beautiful senior Saanvi played by Rashmika Mandanna, her beautiful and cute portrayal of Saanvi will surely remind all the guys their unforgettable crush from college days.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/301216/kirik-party-movie-review-watch-with-your-college-friends-for-maximum-fun.html|title=Kirik Party movie review: Watch with your college friends for maximum fun|work=\ndeccanchronicle}}</ref> This won her [[SIIMA|SIIMA Award for the Best Debut Actress]].<ref name=\"kirik\">{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/news/today/siima-2017awards-kannada.html|title=SIIMA 2017 Kannada winners list&nbsp;\u2014 idlebrain.com news|work=Idlebrain}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Rashmika's first release was [[Harsha (director)|Harsha]]'s ''[[Anjani Putra]]'' opposite [[Puneeth Rajkumar]], which ran for 50-days in some theatres of [[Karnataka]].<ref>https://twitter.com/AppuFc007/status/960142093074161665?s=19</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s Sunayana Suresh wrote that \"Rashmika Mandanna as cute as the leading lady and shows that she has comic timing that can be tapped in to.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/anjaniputhraa/amp_movie_review/62192278.cms|title=Anjaniputra review|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref>\nThe ''Cineloka'''s writer stated that \"Rashmika Mandanna as his love interest plays a good-natured, jaunty girl next door and delivers good performance.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cineloka.co.in/index.php/2017-04-23-04-49-47/movie-reviews/461-anjaniputra-movie-review-cineloka|title=AnjaniPutra Movie Review|work=Cineloka}}</ref>\nThe ''[[New Indian Express]]''`s Sharadhaa claimed that \"This is Rashmika Mandanna\u2019s first movie with Puneeth and she has upped her glam quotient, even while keeping her girl-next-door appeal.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2017/dec/22/anjaniputra-review-this-film-is-for-puneeths-fans-by-a-fan-1734806.amp|title=Anjaniputra' Review|website=Newindianexpress.com}}</ref> it earned her [[Zee Kannada|Zee Kannada Hemmeya Kannadati award for Best Actress]] and [[Awards|Luv lavike Readers Choice Award for Best Actress]].<ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/rashmika-hemmeya-kannadathi-kannada-movie-news-kannada-news-208608</ref><ref>https://www.savasher.com/celebrity-actress/rashmika-mandanna-family-wiki-husband/</ref>\n\nHer next and last release was ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]'' opposite [[Ganesh (actor)|Ganesh]], which ran for 100-days in a couple of theatres,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chitraloka.com/news/17333-chamak-completes-100-days.html|title='CHAMAK' COMPLETES 100 DAYS|work=chitraloka}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/kannada/chamak-world-television-premiere-on-saturday/articleshow/64872482.cms|title=Chamak world television premiere on Saturday \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Chamak\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/chamak-is-in-safe-zone-kannada_amp-news-204535&ved|title=Chamak is in safe zone-Kannada  Movie News|website=IndiaGlitz}}</ref>\nshe receives critical acclaim from critics for her role as Khushi, ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s writer Sunayana Suresh stated that \"Rashmika has done a good job at ensuring the audience are with them throughout\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/chamak/amp_movie_review/62294436.cms|title=#Chamak Movie Review {3.5/5}: Critic Review of #Chamak by Times of India|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref>\nWhile ''[[Bangalore Mirror]]''`s writer Shyam Prasad claimed that \"Rashmika sparkles in acting.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bangaloremirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/reviews/chamak-movie-review-freshly-old-but-charming-enough/articleshow/62300173.cms|title=Chamak movie review: Freshly old, but charming enough|author=Shyam Prasad|website=Bangalore Mirror|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> ''[[The New Indian Express]]''`s \nSharadhaa wrote that \"Rashmika Mandanna emerges as a good artiste in her third outing. The actress, who comes in two shades has taken responsibility for her character, and it shows.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2017/dec/30/chamak-review-a-fresh-take-on-love-1740026.html|title='Chamak' review: A Fresh Take on Love|website=Newindianexpress.com}}</ref> Latter garnered her first nomination for [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Kannada]] at [[65th Filmfare Awards South]]. three consecutive films in [[Kannada]] language all succeeded at the box office makes her 'hat-trick' heroine in [[Kannada film industry]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/rashmika-mandanna-heroine-of-2017-kannada-news-204253|title=Rashmika Mandanna heroine of 2017 \u2013 Kannada Movie News|website=IndiaGlitz.com}}</ref>\n\n===Debut and fame in Telugu: 2018===\n[[File:Rashmikamandanna.jpg|right|175px|thumb|Rashmika during an inauguration of Mugda Arts Store at [[Hyderabad]] in 2018]]\nShe made her [[Telugu cinema|Telugu film]] debut opposite [[Naga Shourya]] with the film titled ''[[Chalo]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sharadhaa|first1=A.|title=Rashmika mandanna \u2019s tollywood debut with Naga Shourya|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2017/mar/16/rashmika-mandanna-s-tollywood-debut-with-naga-shourya-1581751.html|website=The New Indian Express|accessdate=31 March 2017|date=16 March 2017}}</ref>, which ran for 100-days in some theatres,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/chalo-7-days-worldwide-collections-naga-shaurya-starrer-rakes-in-share-of-rs-8-cr/amp_articleshow/62873123.cms|title=Chalo 7 days\u2019 worldwide collections: Naga Shaurya starrer rakes in share of Rs 8 cr  \u2013 Times of India|website=Timesofindia.com}}</ref> critics have been heaped praise on Rashmika for her performance.<ref name=\"Chal\"/><ref name=\"auto\"/> The ''[[Firstpost|First post]]''`s Hemanth Kumar wrote that \"Rashmika makes a terrific debut and she\u2019s a joy to watch on screen\".<ref name=\"Chal\">{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/chalo-movie-review-naga-shaurya-rashmika-mandanna-stand-out-in-this-quirky-comedy-4333869.html|title=Chalo movie review: Naga Shaurya, Rashmika Mandanna stand out in this quirky comedy- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=3 February 2018|website=Firstpost|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> While writer of ''[[The Hindu]]''`s Srivathsan Nadadhur stated that she makes a \"Confident debut\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/chalo-review-being-fair-in-love-and-war/article22634327.ece|title='Chalo' review: Being fair in love and war|first=Srivathsan|last=Nadadhur|date=2 February 2018|accessdate=21 March 2019|website=Thehindu.com}}</ref> ''Idlebrain'''s Jeevi   \nnoted that she was \"very cute and acts well\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/chalo.html|title=Chalo review by jeevi \u2013 Telugu cinema review \u2013 Naga Shaurya and Rashmika Mandanna|website=Idlebrain.com}}</ref>\nThe ''Greatandra'' stated that \"Kannada heroine Rashmika is cute.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.greatandhra.com/movies/reviews/chalo-review-fun-factor-works-out-87269|title=Chalo, Chalo Rating, Chalo Review, Chalo Telugu Review, Naga Shaurya|first=|last=Venkat|date=2 February 2018|website=greatandhra.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> The ''123Telugu'' stated that \"Rashmika makes an impressive debut and suits perfectly in her role.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.123telugu.com/reviews/chalo-telugu-movie-review.html|title=Chalo Telugu Movie Review|date=3 February 2018|website=123telugu.com}}</ref> ''Telugu360'''s editor wrote that \"Rashmika lent good support to Shaurya with her performance. She is bubbly and effervescent in comedy scenes and shows good promise as an actress.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telugu360.com/chalo-movie-review/|title=Chalo Movie Review, Chalo Review Naga Shourya Chalo movie review|date=2 February 2018|website=Telugu360.com}}</ref>\n\nHer next film was ''[[Geetha Govindam]]'' opposite [[Vijay Devarakonda]], which opened to positive reviews and went on to collect over \u20b9130 [[crore]]<ref name=\"Gf\"/> against production budget \u20b95 crore and ran for 100-days in couple of theatres.<ref name=\"Geetha\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/geetha-govindam-box-office-collection-day-8-vijay-starrer-sets-cash-registers-ringing-bakrid-778539 |title=Geetha Govindam is a small budget movie that is made on a shoe-string budget of \u20b95 crore |work=ibtimes.co.in |access-date=23 August 2018}}</ref> \nand brought her much recognition, making her very popular in [[Telangana]] and [[Andhra Pradesh]], alongside she received immense critical appraisal from both critics and audience, ''[[Hindustan Times]]''`s Priyanka Sundar noted that \"Rashmika have taken this solid plot a notch higher with their delightful performances. Rashmika especially will have you rooting for her throughout the film\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/geetha-govindam-movie-review-vijay-deverakonda-rashmika-mandanna-will-win-you-over-in-this-rom-com/story-yUxgQ8qPoaczB4Bra6IYzO.html|title=Geetha Govindam movie review: Vijay Deverakonda, Rashmika Mandanna will win you over in this rom-com|date=15 August 2018|website=M.hindustantimes.com}}</ref> The writer of ''[[The Times of India]]'' stated that \"Rashmika too sparkles and the scenes between the two is what makes Geetha Govindam so likeable\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/geetha-govindam/movie-review/65411950.cms|title=Geetha Govindam Review {3.5/5}: If you love rom-coms, you're going to lap this up. A big thumbs up!|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref> ''[[The Indian Express]]'' claimed that \"Rashmika as uncompromising Geetha also does a pretty good job\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/geetha-govindam-movie-review-vijay-deverakonda-rashmika-mandanna-5308099/|title=Geetha Govindam movie review: Vijay Deverakonda starrer is a charming romantic comedy|date=15 August 2018|website=Indianexpress.com}}</ref> ''[[The Hindu]]'' stated that \"She has an easy screen presence and the potential to handle more well-written parts\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/geetha-govindam-review-this-vijay-deverakonda-film-is-an-antithesis-to-arjun-reddy/article24696712.ece|title='Geetha Govindam' review: The good guy takes over|first=Sangeetha Devi|last=Dundoo|date=15 August 2018|website=Thehindu.com}}</ref> ''[[Firstpost|First post]]''`s writer noted that \"Rashmika and Vijay, who makes it an enjoyable watch. Being paired on-screen for the first time, they  performed their respective roles very well.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/geetha-govindam-movie-review-vijay-deverakondas-performance-proves-he-is-not-a-one-hit-wonder-4970831.html|title=Geetha Govindam movie review: Vijay Deverakonda's performance proves he is not a one hit wonder- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=15 August 2018|website=Firstpost|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Rashmika mandanna at the Promotions of Devadas.png|right|150px|thumb|Rashmika at promotion of ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]'' movie in 2018]]\nHer next release was multi-starrer big budget film titled ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]'', she shared a space with [[Akkineni Nagarjuna]] and [[Nani (actor)|Nani]] as one of the main lead in the film along [[Akanksha Singh]]. It marked her hat-trick hit film in her career in [[Telugu film industry]] according to few regional reliable sources. She had less screen space, though received critical appraisal for her performance. ''Chitramala''`s writer noted that \"Rashmika Mandanna impressed in her role and made her presence felt.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chitramala.in/devadas-telugu-movie-review-276459.html/amp|title=Devadas Telugu Movie Review|date=27 September 2018|website=Chitramala.in}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s writer states that \"Rashmika deserved better character arc, even though she plays a people of prominence.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/devadas/movieshow/65977659.cms|title=Devadas Movie Review {3.5/5}: The Deva and Das show is thoroughly entertaining|website=M.timesofindia.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Continued success and Tamil debut (2019-20) ===\nRashmika started 2019 acting in ''[[Yajamana (2019 film)|Yajamana]]'', Kannada language film opposite [[Darshan (actor)|Darshan]], which received decent reviews from the both audience and critics upon the release. And began earning a profit within five-days of its release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/yajamana-box-office-collection-darshans-film-profit-zone-just-5-days-end-1st-week-high-note-793347|title=Yajamana box office collection: Darshan's film in profit zone in just 5 days, to end 1st week on high note|first=Prakash|last=Upadhyaya|date=7 March 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> Later it collected over \u20b950 crore<ref name=\"Yajj\"/> against production budget \u20b918 crore<ref name=\"Dar\">{{cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2019/yajamana-day-14-box-office-collection-darshan-continues-to-rule-in-karnataka-slow-run-in-the-us-283815.html|title=Yajamana Day 14 Box Office Collection \u2013 Darshan Continues To Rule In Karnataka But Slow Run In The US \u2013 Filmibeat|date=14 March 2019|website=Filmibeat.com|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref> and ran for over 100-days in some theatres in [[Karnataka]].<ref name=\"Yajj\">{{cite web|url=https://newsable.asianetnews.com/entertainment/yajamana-grosses-rs-50-crore-becomes-darshan-s-first-movie-to-cross-the-mark-kgf-rajakumara-the-villain-pod1xd|title=Yajamana grosses Rs 50 crore, becomes Darshan's first movie to cross the mark|website=Asianet News Network Pvt Ltd|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref>Darshan's Yajamana hits the 100-day mark - https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/darshans-yajamana-hits-the-100-day-mark/articleshow/69375318.cms</ref>\nShe has been received critical acclaim for her performance as Kaveri, ''[[Times Of India]]'' editor claimed that \"Rashmika Mandanna is cute and her pairing with Darshan works well\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/yajamana/movie-review/68213387.cms|title=Yajamana Review {3.5/5}: A must-watch for fans of commercial cinema|accessdate=21 March 2019|website=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref> The ''[[New Indian Express]]'' editor noticed that \"Rashmika Mandanna is allicient as the love interest and justifies the village girl\u2019s character\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2019/mar/02/yajamana-review-this-darshan-starrer-is-a-mass-entertainer-with-social-message-1945439.amp|title='Yajamana' review: This Darshan-starrer is a mass entertainer with social message - The New Indian Express|website=www.newindianexpress.com}}</ref> In 2019, her next film was ''[[Dear Comrade]]'' opposite [[Vijay Devarakonda]], which opened to mixed reviews from  both critics and audience. It went on to become a financial failure and touted as first flop at box office in Rashmika's film career. Even though she received overwhelming critical acclaim for her performance in the film as 'Lilly'.<ref>https://www.tollywood.net/article/dear-comrade-to-face-50-loss-in-ceded-huge-disaster/49355/amp</ref> It earned her first [[Award|behindwood's gold medal award]] for best actor critics choice.<ref name=\" BG\">https://m.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/slideshow/winners-of-7th-behindwoods-gold-medals/rashmika-mandanna-behindwoods-gold-medal-winner-2019.html</ref> She has gone on to win awards honouring her cinematic contributions, including ''Just for Women'''s Magazine \"Sensation of the Year Award\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jfwonline.com/article/the-future-of-cinema-rashmika-mandanna/|title=The future of cinema; Rashmika Mandanna|website=JFW Just for women|access-date=2019-11-30}}</ref> and the \"Youth Icon\" award in [[Colors Tamil]]'s \"Wonder Women\" Awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/vijays-wife-ajiths-viswasam-director-rashmika-keerthy-suresh-celebs-wonder-women-awards-807492|title=From Vijay's wife to Ajith's Viswasam director, Rashmika Mandanna to Keerthy Suresh, celebs galore at WW Awards|last=Upadhyaya|first=Prakash|date=2019-10-21|website=International Business Times, India Edition|language=english|access-date=2019-11-30}}</ref> She was invited to participate in a panel discussion (\"Leading Actress\") at the 2019 [[International Indian Film Academy Awards]] (the award function's Golden Jubilee) along with [[Nithya Menen]] moderated by the Indian film critic [[Baradwaj Rangan]], which was organized in [[Goa]].<ref>https://www.filmibeat.com/interviews/iffi-2019-kannada-actress-rashmika-mandanna-interview-exclusive-filmibeat-292252.html\n</ref>\n\nIn 2020 Rashmika starred opposite [[Mahesh Babu]] in ''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]'', which opened to decent reviews from audience and critics upon the release and went on to become one of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest grossing films]] in the [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film industry,<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sarileru-neekevvaru-9-day-box-office-collection-anil-ravipudi-scores-career-best-mahesh-babu-811970</ref> and emerged as Rashmika's career highest profit erner to date by collecting \u20b92 billion in just 10-days.<ref name=\"SLN\">https://www.businesstoday.in/trending/box-office/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-box-office-collection-allu-arjun-film-ahead-of-mahesh-babu-sarileru-neekevvaru/story/394286.html</ref><ref name=\"SLN 1st week collection\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/sankranti-telugu-releases-ala-vaikuntapuramloo-sarileru-neekevvaru-strike-gold-at-the-box-office/story-Bm8033vi57uLu8fTVHkqJK.html|title=Sankranti Telugu releases Ala Vaikuntapuramloo, Sarileru Neekevvaru strike gold at the box office|website=Hindustan Times|date=20 January 2020|access-date=21 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"SLN 3 Days\">{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/mahesh-babu-film-sarileru-neekevvaru-earns-rs-103-crore-6216179/|title=Mahesh Babu film Sarileru Neekevvaru earns Rs 103 crore|website=Indian Express|date=14 January 2020|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/sarileru-neekevvaru-box-office-collection-mahesh-babu-and-rashmika-mandanna-starrer-hits-the-100-crore-mark-in-three-days/articleshow/73247929.cms|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru Box-Office Collection: Mahesh Babu and Rashmika Mandanna starrer hits the 100-crore mark in three days|website=The Times of India|date=14 January 2020|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref> And went on to collect over \u20b92.6 billion in 50-days theatrical run at worldwide box office.<ref name=\"SLN 50-days collection The Statesman\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thestatesman.com/entertainment/southern_cinema/sarileru-neekevvaru-mahesh-babu-celebrates-50-days-box-office-1502861238.html|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru: Mahesh Babu celebrates 50 Days at box office. It has grossed Rs 260 crore till now|website=[[The Statesman (India)|The Statesman]]|date=29 February 2020|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"SLN 50-days collection India TV\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/regional-cinema/mahesh-babu-celebrates-50-days-sarileru-neekevvaru-box-office-593698|title=Mahesh Babu celebrates 50 Days of Sarileru Neekevvaru at box office|website=[[India TV]]|date=29 February 2020|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"SLN 50-days collection Outlook India\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/mahesh-babu-celebrates-50-days-of-sarileru-neekevvaru-at-box-office/1747919|title=Mahesh Babu celebrates 50 Days of ''Sarileru Neekevvaru'' at box office|website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook India]]|date=29 February 2020|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref> The reviewer of ''[[Times Of India]]'' Neeshita Nyayapati, stated \"Rashmika Mandanna woos, gets hyper, dances, has a catch-line, all for the male lead, but why she exists in this tale, other than to fawn over him is a mystery.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/sarileru-neekevvaru/movie-review/73198148.cms|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru Movie Review|website=The Times of India|date=11 January 2020|access-date=16 January 2020}}</ref> The editor of ''[[India Today]]'' Janani K, claimed that \"We see Rashmika playing a typical 'loosu ponnu' (read: A mindless heroine who acts like a kid) who keeps stalking Mahesh Babu.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/sarileru-neekevvaru-movie-review-mahesh-babu-film-is-utterly-disappointing-1635966-2020-01-11|title=Sarileru Neekevvaru Movie Review|website=India Today|date=11 January 2020|access-date=16 January 2020}}</ref> Whereas, the editor of ''[[Hans India]]'' stated that \"Rashmika Mandanna has impressed with her performance.\"<ref>https://www.thehansindia.com/movie-reviews/sarileru-neekevvaru-movie-review-rating-35-76527\nhttps://www.thehansindia.com/movie-reviews/sarileru-neekevvaru-movie-review-rating-35-76527</ref> Her next Telugu film in 2020 was ''[[Bheeshma (2020 film)|Bheeshma]]'' opposite [[Nithiin]], which opened to positive response from the both critics and audience.<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bheeshma-movie-review-rating-by-audience-live-updates-813649\n</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/bheeshma-box-office-nithiins-highest-opening-in-the-telugu-states/articleshow/74253897.cms</ref> The film went on to become a financial hit at worldwide box office by collecting over \u20b950 crore.<ref>https://telugu.news18.com/news/movies/nithiin-bheeshma-movie-collects-50-crore-gross-world-wide-for-first-week-sr-464782.html</ref><ref>https://telugu.samayam.com/telugu-movies/cinema-news/nithiin-and-rashmika-starrer-bheeshma-movie-collects-rs-50-crores-gross-world-wind/articleshow/74391410.cms</ref> She received praise for her performance as Chaitra. The ''[[Firstpost]]'''s editor Hemanth Kumar praised her chemistry with Nithiin.<ref>https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bheeshma-movie-review-nithiin-rashmika-mandannas-romantic-drama-is-a-breezy-entertainer-8070741.html</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!Year!! Films !! Roles !! Director(s) !! Languages \n!Notes\n|-\n|2016\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Kirik Party]]''\n| Saanvi Joseph\n| [[Rishab Shetty]]\n|rowspan='3'|[[Kannada language|Kannada]]\n|Kannada Debut\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Anjani Putra]]''\n| Geetha\n| [[Harsha (director)|Harsha]]\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Chamak (film)|Chamak]]''\n| Kushi\n| [[Suni (director)|Suni]]\n|Nominated- [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Kannada|Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Kannada]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2018\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Chalo]]''\n| L. Karthika\n| Venky Kudumula\n| rowspan='3'|[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|Telugu Debut\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Geetha Govindam]]''\n| Geetha\n| [[Parasuram (director)|Parasuram]]\n|Won \u2013 [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South|Filmfare Award for Best Actress (Critics) - Telugu]]<br />Nominated- [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Telugu|Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Telugu]]\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Devadas (2018 film)|Devadas]]''\n| Inspector Pooja\n| Sriram Aditya\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n!scope=\"row\" |''[[Yajamana (2019 film)|Yajamana]]''\n| Kaveri\n|[[Pon Kumaran]] <br> [[V. Harikrishna]